SECTION 21 — TORQUE TUNING STRATEGY (DEPLOYMENT)
============================================================

PHASE 1 — ZERO ASSIST
--------------------------------
SET:
- max_torque = 2 Nm

GOAL:
- System produces no noticeable force
- Validate stability only

--------------------------------
PHASE 2 — LIGHT ASSIST
--------------------------------
INCREMENT:
- 2 → 5 → 8 Nm

TUNE:
- Increase Kp → responsiveness
- Increase Kd → smoothness (removes jerk)

--------------------------------
PHASE 3 — INTENT MATCHING
--------------------------------
GOAL:
- Assist begins exactly when user initiates motion

ADJUST:
- Velocity thresholds (Jetson)
- Reduce delay between detection and torque

--------------------------------
PHASE 4 — REGEN TUNING
--------------------------------
WHEN braking (negative velocity):
- Apply small negative torque

RULE:
- Must feel natural
- Never resist user strongly

--------------------------------
PHASE 5 — MAX SAFE LIMIT
--------------------------------
SET HARD CAP:
- 10–15 Nm (V1 safe range)

DO NOT EXCEED until:
- Full system stability verified

--------------------------------
CONTROL FEEL TARGET
--------------------------------
SUCCESS FEELS LIKE:
- “My leg, but stronger”

FAILURE FEELS LIKE:
- “Something is pushing/pulling me”

--------------------------------
TUNING ERROR DIAGNOSIS
--------------------------------
Jerky motion:
→ Kd too low

Lag:
→ Kp too low

Oscillation:
→ Kp too high

Resistance feeling:
→ Torque too high

--------------------------------
FINAL RULE
--------------------------------
SYSTEM MUST:
- Assist motion
- NEVER override user intent

